# Advanced CSS Selectors and Pseudo-classes

## Introduction

After mastering basic CSS, we'll learn about **Advanced Selectors** and **Pseudo-classes**.

## Advanced Selectors

### Descendant Selector
```css
div p { color: blue; }
```

### Child Selector (>)
```css
div > p { color: red; }
```

### Attribute Selectors
```css
[type="text"] { border: 1px solid #ccc; }
[href^="https"] { color: green; }
```

## Pseudo-classes

```css
a:hover { color: red; }
input:focus { border: 2px solid blue; }
p:first-child { font-weight: bold; }
li:nth-child(even) { background-color: #f0f0f0; }
```

## Pseudo-elements

```css
p::before { content: "Note: "; }
p::first-letter { font-size: 2em; color: red; }
```

## Summary

Advanced selectors and pseudo-classes help you target elements more precisely!
